data.text:
Eye of Darkness was the fourth and final story in the audio anthology Dark Eyes 4. It was written by Matt Fitton and featured Paul McGann as the Eighth Doctor, Sorcha Cusack as Molly O'Sullivan, Nicola Walker as Liv Chenka and David Sibley as The Eminence.

Publisher's summary[]

It's the endgame. Truths will be revealed, and a hero will make the ultimate sacrifice.

Plot[]

to be added

Cast[]

The Doctor - Paul McGann

Liv Chenka - Nicola Walker

Mary Carter - Sorcha Cusack

The Dalek Time Controller / The Dalek Supreme / The Daleks - Nicholas Briggs

The Eminence / Markus Schriver - David Sibley

Anya - Susannah Harker

Brother Callis - Derek Hutchinson

Crew[]

Cover Art - Tom Webster

Director - Ken Bentley

Executive Producers - Nicholas Briggs and Jason Haigh-Ellery

Music and Sound Design - Howard Carter

Producer - David Richardson

Writer - Matt Fitton

Worldbuilding[]

Anya comes from Nixyce II.

Notes[]

This is the final story to feature Molly O'Sullivan.

Continuity[]

Liv mentions that the Eye of Orion was said by the Doctor to be the most peaceful place in the universe. (TV: The Five Doctors)

Shriver mentions the events of the last time he met Liv. (AUDIO: Masterplan)

The Dalek Time Controller mentions seeing future incarnations of the Doctor. (PROSE: The Dalek Generation)

Liv notes that she has endured Dalek occupation. (AUDIO: The Traitor)

Seeing off the Eminence, the Doctor points out that it will eventually stop back where they found it at the Orpheus. (AUDIO: Time's Horizon)

A new Dalek Time Strategist is created from Adelaine Dutemps. (AUDIO: The Monster of Montmartre)
